Now let me create the test list. I'll walk through the spec systematically:

**Quote rules:**
- Empty list → 5 G fee only
- Single item base premiums (sword 100, amulet 60, staff 80, potion 40)
- Component pricing (rune/moonstone: 25 each, block of 3 alike = 60)
- Component block examples: 2 runes = 50, 3 runes = 60, 4 runes = 100, 7 runes = 175
- Mixed components: 2 runes + 1 moonstone = 75 (no block), 3 runes + 3 moonstones = 120 (two blocks)
- Cursed +50%
- High enchantment (≥5) +30%
- Loyalty discount (≥2 years) -20%
- First insurance +10% (per item)
- Follow-up contract -15% (policy-wide after first)
- Processing fee 5 G
- Rounding up (in MHPCO's favor for premiums)
- Multi-item modifier scope: cursed sword + amulet = 160 base + 50 (50% of cursed sword base) = 210 before fee
- Threshold tests (exactly 2 years, enchantment exactly 5)
- Newcomer cursed sword integration → 165
- Long-standing customer second contract integration → 160
- Unknown item type → error

**Claim rules:**
- Deductible 100 G per damage event
- Cap = 2× insurance sum
- Enchantment ≥8 → 50% payout
- Dragon material → full reimbursement
- Standard examples (regular sword 500 → 400, rune 200 → 100)
- Enchantment + dragon material combinations
- Dragon attack on two items (sword 500 + amulet 300 → 600)
- Multiple items same type (two swords)
- Damages array more entries than insured → error
- Cap exhaustion (two successive claims)
- Rounding down for payouts (350.5 → 350)
- Dragon-material sword enchant 8, damage 1000 → 400
- Cap based on unmodified insurance value
- Block components: insurance sum still based on full value
- Damage to item not in policy → error
- Negative damage amount → error

